@flexiarg vsatlatarium/cached-layout-computation
@title Cached Layout Computation
@audience platform engineers, digital library architects
@tone plain-analytic
@style design-pattern
@sigils [⚡/缓]
@references [vsatlatarium/cluster-as-story vsatlas/proof-of-concept-scope]

! conclusion:
  Cache the O(N²) force-directed layout across requests so the planetarium
  loads instantly when story data has not changed.

  + context: You are serving a 3D visualisation from SSR where layout computation is the bottleneck. This does not apply to client-side-only visualisations where the cost is borne by the browser.
  + IF:
    The force-directed simulation (spring forces, repulsion, centering)
    runs on every request, consuming CPU proportional to scene count
    squared.

  + HOWEVER:
    Story data changes rarely — most requests see the same constellation.

  + THEN:
    Fingerprint the inputs (story IDs, scene counts, link IDs, view mode,
    pilot filter) and cache the computed layout in a globalThis-backed
    in-memory store. Invalidate automatically when the fingerprint changes.

  + BECAUSE:
    First-load computes; subsequent loads return instantly. This turned a
    200% CPU incident on a 2-CPU host into sub-millisecond cache hits.

  + STATUS:
    status[ready]
    evidence[layoutCache.ts — globalThis store surviving Vite SSR module re-evaluation]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Add cache-hit/miss logging to measure real-world hit rate.]
    next[Consider persisting the cache to disk for cold-start performance after server restart.]
